        "client_msg_id": "c8926efc-c0f2-4598-b05c-e067727ec083",
        "type": "message",
        "text": "Ahhhh Imposter Syndrome (sort of) - a challenge so many of us deal with on a regular basis. Despite not having my own project or NL, I am always so cautious of this in general when promoting the company I work for (or myself on LI.)\n\nIf you’re providing value - don’t be afraid to talk about your newsletter. In fact, you should definitely give away some of that content for free in other places and then let people know that if they want more, they can subscribe. \n\nI’d also say it’s helpful when you can incorporate and rise up others in the process. For example, doing a content roundup with the best CM plays you saw this year and tagging all the people and companies who contributed to each play. No one will think twice if you ask for a newsletter sign up after you…\na.) provided value\nb.) rose others up in the process\n\nBest of luck!",
        "user": "U013P4Q9YTU",
        "ts": "1608670323.347800",
